div1.p:
1892, by Col. E.C. Mason, 3d Inf., Ft.

Snelling, Minn. Summary is Very Good;

habits Excellent. No peculiar fitness.

[unclear] was appointed assistant surgeon, with the rank of 1st Lieut. to rank from June 16, 1875;

Accepted his commission.       July 3, 1875;

Promoted to be assistant surgeon with the rank of Captain,    June 26, 1880;

Promoted to be surgeon with the rank of Major,    Dec. 2, 1893;

Died, at Washington, D.C.       Nov. 23, 1902.
